// nodule: lsp.sync
// **Document sync** (M-310; FR-S5; SC-5): the text ‚Üí `Node` pipeline the LSP server runs on
// `textDocument/didOpen` / `didChange` / `didClose`, now that RFC-0011 r3 + RFC-0001 r4 give the
// surface a path into L0 (parse ‚Üí check ‚Üí elaborate).
//
// On each edit the server re-analyzes the *whole* document (full sync ‚Äî `TextDocumentSyncKind.Full`)
// and pushes `textDocument/publishDiagnostics`. The diagnostics are **honest about their spans**:
// - a **parse/lex** failure carries a **real range** (the L1 lexer tracks `line:col`, `Pos`);
// - a **type-check** failure carries a best-effort range at the offending function's `fn <name>`
//   declaration (the checker tracks the failing *function* but not yet the failing *sub-expression*
//   span ‚Äî flagged, not fabricated: the precise sub-span awaits the checker carrying spans), with
//   the function name in `data.breadcrumb`;
// - a **clean** nodule yields **no** diagnostics.
//
// The parser is fail-fast (one error at a time); a recovering parser that reports many diagnostics
// at once is a later refinement ‚Äî recorded, not silently implied.
// @summary: best-effort transpilation via mycelium-transpile (M-873). Declared,
// unvalidated ‚Äî no Mycelium parser/typechecker confirms this output; see the
// accompanying .gap.json for every construct this pass could not express.
nodule lsp.sync;


